<p>
In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title=3D"Mathemati=
cs">mathematics</a>, the <b>Laplace transform</b>, named after <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre-Simon_Laplace" title=3D"Pierre-Simon La=
place">Pierre-Simon Laplace</a> (<span class=3D"rt-commentedText nowrap"><s=
pan class=3D"IPA nopopups noexcerpt" lang=3D"en-fonipa"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title=3D"Help:IPA/English">/<span s=
tyle=3D"border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title=3D"'l' in 'lie'">l</span><spa=
n title=3D"/=C9=99/: 'a' in 'about'">=C9=99</span><span title=3D"/=CB=88/: =
primary stress follows">=CB=88</span><span title=3D"'p' in 'pie'">p</span><=
span title=3D"'l' in 'lie'">l</span><span title=3D"/=C9=91=CB=90/: 'a' in '=
father'">=C9=91=CB=90</span><span title=3D"'s' in 'sigh'">s</span></span>/<=
/a></span></span>), is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral=
_transform" title=3D"Integral transform">integral transform</a> that conver=
ts a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Function_(mathematics)" title=
=3D"Function (mathematics)">function</a> of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Real_number" title=3D"Real number">real</a> <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variable_(mathematics)" title=3D"Variable (mathematic=
s)">variable</a> (usually <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-=
inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=
=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
ext=3D"{\displaystyle t}">
