<p>The Laplace transform is named after <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Mathematician" title=3D"Mathematician">mathematician</a> and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomer" title=3D"Astronomer">astronom=
er</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre-Simon_Laplace" title=
=3D"Pierre-Simon Laplace">Pierre-Simon, Marquis de Laplace</a>, who used a =
similar transform in his work on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/P=
robability_theory" title=3D"Probability theory">probability theory</a>.<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Laplace_transform#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Laplace wrote extensively ab=
out the use of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Generating_function=
" title=3D"Generating function">generating functions</a>  (1814), and the i=
ntegral form of the Laplace transform evolved naturally as a result.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Laplace_transform#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Laplace's use of generating functions was similar to what is now kno=
wn as the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z-transform" title=3D"Z-=
transform">z-transform</a>, and he gave little attention to the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_variable" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Continuous variable">continuous variable</a> case which was discusse=
d by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niels_Henrik_Abel" title=3D"N=
iels Henrik Abel">Niels Henrik Abel</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laplace_transform#cite_not=
e-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>
</p><p>From 1744, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonhard_Euler" =
title=3D"Leonhard Euler">Leonhard Euler</a> investigated integrals of the f=
orm
