gebra)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Ring (abstract algebra)">ring</a> of=
 functions on the positive half-line. The resulting <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Convolution_quotient" title=3D"Convolution quotient">spac=
e of abstract operators</a> is exactly equivalent to Laplace space, but in =
this construction the forward and reverse transforms never need to be expli=
citly defined (avoiding the related difficulties with proving convergence).=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-22" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Laplace_transform#cite_note-22"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
