 theorem</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morera%27s_theore=
m" title=3D"Morera's theorem">Morera's theorem</a>.
</p><p>Similarly, the set of values for which <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>F<=
/i>(<i>s</i>)</span> converges (conditionally or absolutely) is known as th=
e region of conditional convergence, or simply the <b>region of convergence=
</b> (ROC). If the Laplace transform converges (conditionally) at <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml"><i>s</i> =3D <i>s</i><sub>0</sub></span>, then it automatica=
lly converges for all <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>s</i></span> with <span cl=
