        <mi>Z</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow>
            <mo fence=3D"true" stretchy=3D"true" symmetric=3D"true"></mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mrow>
                  <mi>V</mi>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>s</mi>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <mi>I</mi>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi>s</mi>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>|</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msub>
              <mi>V</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>0</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Z(s)=3D\left.=
{V(s) \over I(s)}\right|_{V_{0}=3D0}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/6711003350f4559c32bca99676f9ae3e2f000df7" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -3.005ex; width:18.618ex; height:6.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle Z=
(s)=3D\left.{V(s) \over I(s)}\right|_{V_{0}=3D0}.}"></span>
</p><p>Using this definition and the previous equation, we find:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle Z(s)=3D{\frac {1}{sC}},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>Z</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mi>C</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Z(s)=3D{\frac=
 {1}{sC}},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b9aace1d29c498b7585d461970a874aa2ca5fefe" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.005ex; width:12.018ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle Z=
(s)=3D{\frac {1}{sC}},}"></span>
which is the correct expression for the complex impedance of a capacitor. I=
n addition, the Laplace transform has large applications in control theory.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Impulse_response">Impulse r=
esponse</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLapl=
ace_transform&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D25" title=3D"Edit section: Im=
pulse response"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<p>Consider a linear time-invariant system with <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Transfer_function" title=3D"Transfer function">transfer funct=
ion</a>
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle H(s)=3D{\frac {1}{(s+\alpha )(s+\beta )}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>H</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle H(s)=3D{\frac=
 {1}{(s+\alpha )(s+\beta )}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/553a78b681373612c87e6d31f6a2b52080d1871b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:23.845ex; height:6.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle H=
(s)=3D{\frac {1}{(s+\alpha )(s+\beta )}}.}"></span>
</p><p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impulse_response" title=
=3D"Impulse response">impulse response</a> is simply the inverse Laplace tr=
ansform of this transfer function:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle h(t)=3D{\mathcal {L}}^{-1}\{H(s)\}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>h</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>t</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi class=3D"MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant=3D"script">L</m=
i>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">{</mo>
        <mi>H</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">}</mo>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle h(t)=3D{\math=
cal {L}}^{-1}\{H(s)\}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3c2fcfed3bfaf30f53ccc8c2b9d1064a4c51b9dc" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:18.958ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle h=
(t)=3D{\mathcal {L}}^{-1}\{H(s)\}.}"></span>
</p>
<dl><dt>Partial fraction expansion</dt></dl>
<p>To evaluate this inverse transform, we begin by expanding <span class=3D=
"texhtml"><i>H</i>(<i>s</i>)</span> using the method of partial fraction ex=
pansion,
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\frac {1}{(s+\alpha )(s+\beta )}}=3D{P \over s+\alpha }+{R \ov=
er s+\beta }.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>P</mi>
            <mrow>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>R</mi>
            <mrow>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{(s=
+\alpha )(s+\beta )}}=3D{P \over s+\alpha }+{R \over s+\beta }.}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/18e59114cab3e1242b577c78ce884fe1225b4871" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:34.075ex; height:6.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\frac {1}{(s+\alpha )(s+\beta )}}=3D{P \over s+\alpha }+{R \over s+\beta }.=
}"></span>
</p><p>The unknown constants <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>P</i></span> and <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></span> are the <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Residue_(complex_analysis)" title=3D"Residue (complex analysis)=
">residues</a> located at the corresponding poles of the transfer function.=
 Each residue represents the relative contribution of that <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_singularity" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Mathematical singularity">singularity</a> to the transfer function's=
 overall shape.
</p><p>By the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Residue_theorem" tit=
le=3D"Residue theorem">residue theorem</a>, the inverse Laplace transform d=
epends only upon the poles and their residues. To find the residue <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml"><i>P</i></span>, we multiply both sides of the equation by =
<span class=3D"texhtml"><i>s</i> + <i>=CE=B1</i></span> to get
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\frac {1}{s+\beta }}=3DP+{R(s+\alpha ) \over s+\beta }.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>R</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi>s</mi>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{s+=
\beta }}=3DP+{R(s+\alpha ) \over s+\beta }.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/da6d4af6ff6e108f5079733011d48d7fd47e35c5" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:24.258ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\frac {1}{s+\beta }}=3DP+{R(s+\alpha ) \over s+\beta }.}"></span>
</p><p>Then by letting <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>s</i> =3D =E2=88=92<i>=CE=
=B1</i></span>, the contribution from <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></spa=
n> vanishes and all that is left is
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle P=3D\left.{1 \over s+\beta }\right|_{s=3D-\alpha }=3D{1 \over \=
beta -\alpha }.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow>
            <mo fence=3D"true" stretchy=3D"true" symmetric=3D"true"></mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mn>1</mn>
                <mrow>
                  <mi>s</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>|</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>s</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle P=3D\left.{1 =
\over s+\beta }\right|_{s=3D-\alpha }=3D{1 \over \beta -\alpha }.}</annotat=
ion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/667e086ca22b4819f4188e6a30c83baa4fbb329d" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:26.443ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle P=
=3D\left.{1 \over s+\beta }\right|_{s=3D-\alpha }=3D{1 \over \beta -\alpha =
}.}"></span>
</p><p>Similarly, the residue <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></span> is gi=
ven by
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle R=3D\left.{1 \over s+\alpha }\right|_{s=3D-\beta }=3D{1 \over \=
alpha -\beta }.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mrow>
            <mo fence=3D"true" stretchy=3D"true" symmetric=3D"true"></mo>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mn>1</mn>
                <mrow>
                  <mi>s</mi>
                  <mo>+</mo>
                  <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>|</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>s</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle R=3D\left.{1 =
\over s+\alpha }\right|_{s=3D-\beta }=3D{1 \over \alpha -\beta }.}</annotat=
ion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/09980f06092ea8dccbaa90eaf11ceb6cc7225b4f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.671ex; width:26.508ex; height:6.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle R=
=3D\left.{1 \over s+\alpha }\right|_{s=3D-\beta }=3D{1 \over \alpha -\beta =
}.}"></span>
</p><p>Note that
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle R=3D{-1 \over \beta -\alpha }=3D-P}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mi>=CE=B1<!-- =CE=B1 --></mi>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>P</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle R=3D{-1 \over=
 \beta -\alpha }=3D-P}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/78c637470458d06ed421d04e21d52a9add74e4bf" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:18.011ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle R=
=3D{-1 \over \beta -\alpha }=3D-P}"></span>
and so the substitution of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>R</i></span> and <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml"><i>P</i></span> into the expanded expression for <span =
class=3D"texhtml"><i>H</i>(<i>s</i>)</span> gives
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle H(s)=3D\left({\frac {1}{\beta -\alpha }}\right)\cdot \left({1 \=
over s+\alpha }-{1 \over s+\beta }\right).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>H</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>s</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
